WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.080
Give ear to my words, O Lord, consider my groaning.

2
00:00:04.080 --> 00:00:08.960
Give attention to the sound of my cry, my king and my God,

3
00:00:08.960 --> 00:00:11.200
for to you do I pray.

4
00:00:11.200 --> 00:00:14.280
O Lord, in the morning you hear my voice.

5
00:00:14.280 --> 00:00:18.100
In the morning I prepare a sacrifice for you and watch.

6
00:00:18.100 --> 00:00:21.320
For you are not a God who delights in wickedness.

7
00:00:21.320 --> 00:00:23.600
Evil may not dwell with you.

8
00:00:23.600 --> 00:00:26.680
The boastful shall not stand before your eyes.

9
00:00:26.680 --> 00:00:29.060
You hate all evil doers.

10
00:00:29.060 --> 00:00:31.420
You destroy those who speak lies.

11
00:00:31.420 --> 00:00:35.580
The Lord appores the bloodthirsty and deceitful man.

12
00:00:35.580 --> 00:00:38.540
But I, through the abundance of your steadfast love,

13
00:00:38.540 --> 00:00:40.220
will enter your house.

14
00:00:40.220 --> 00:00:44.260
I will bow down toward your holy temple in the fear of you.

15
00:00:44.260 --> 00:00:46.900
Lead me, O Lord, in your righteousness,

16
00:00:46.900 --> 00:00:48.540
because of my enemies.

17
00:00:48.540 --> 00:00:50.980
Make your way straight before me.

18
00:00:50.980 --> 00:00:53.460
For there is no truth in their mouth.

19
00:00:53.460 --> 00:00:55.820
Their inmost self is destruction.

20
00:00:55.820 --> 00:00:58.080
Their throat is an open grave.

21
00:00:58.080 --> 00:01:00.240
They flatter with their tongue.

22
00:01:00.240 --> 00:01:02.820
Make them bear their guilt, O God.

23
00:01:02.820 --> 00:01:05.000
Let them fall by their own counsels

24
00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:07.440
because of the abundance of their transgressions,

25
00:01:07.440 --> 00:01:10.960
cast them out, for they have rebelled against you.

26
00:01:10.960 --> 00:01:13.920
But let all who take refuge in you rejoice.

27
00:01:13.920 --> 00:01:17.020
Let them ever sing for joy and spread your protection

28
00:01:17.020 --> 00:01:21.160
over them that those who love your name may exalt in you.

29
00:01:21.160 --> 00:01:23.400
For you bless the righteous, O Lord.

30
00:01:23.400 --> 00:01:26.240
You cover him with favor as with a shield.

31
00:01:26.240 --> 00:01:28.000
This is the word of the Lord.

32
00:01:28.040 --> 00:01:28.960
Thanks be to God.

33
00:01:30.040 --> 00:01:30.880
Thank you, Ali.

34
00:01:32.880 --> 00:01:35.320
Well, what we just read in Psalm five,

35
00:01:36.480 --> 00:01:39.040
some of the very same themes are expressed

36
00:01:39.040 --> 00:01:40.520
in the Lord's Prayer.

37
00:01:40.520 --> 00:01:43.040
So we typically pray before we come

38
00:01:43.040 --> 00:01:44.280
to the preaching of God's words.

39
00:01:44.280 --> 00:01:46.320
I'd like for us to pray the very words

40
00:01:46.320 --> 00:01:47.800
of the Lord's Prayer this morning.

41
00:01:47.800 --> 00:01:49.760
So let's pray together.

42
00:01:49.760 --> 00:01:54.760
Our Father who art in heaven, hallowed be thy name.

43
00:01:54.840 --> 00:01:56.560
Thy kingdom come.

44
00:01:56.560 --> 00:02:00.840
Thy will be done on earth as it is in heaven.

45
00:02:00.840 --> 00:02:03.680
Give us this day our daily bread

46
00:02:03.680 --> 00:02:06.200
and forgive us our trespasses

47
00:02:06.200 --> 00:02:10.000
as we forgive those who trespass against us.

48
00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:15.000
And lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil.

49
00:02:15.040 --> 00:02:18.960
For thine is the kingdom, the power, and the glory

50
00:02:18.960 --> 00:02:20.840
forever and ever.

51
00:02:20.840 --> 00:02:21.680
Amen.

52
00:02:23.920 --> 00:02:26.400
Or down a few in number this morning.

53
00:02:26.400 --> 00:02:28.280
So you felt a bit far away.

54
00:02:28.280 --> 00:02:29.720
So I thought I'd get a bit closer to you.

55
00:02:29.720 --> 00:02:33.120
So I'm gonna speak from about here if that is okay.

56
00:02:34.360 --> 00:02:37.720
So we're looking together at Psalm five.

57
00:02:37.720 --> 00:02:40.720
And really the kind of theme is,

58
00:02:40.720 --> 00:02:42.480
I mean, if you've got an ESV Bible in front of you,

59
00:02:42.480 --> 00:02:46.080
it may have a title which is lead me in your righteousness.

60
00:02:46.080 --> 00:02:48.520
I've just kind of taken that as a theme for today

61
00:02:48.520 --> 00:02:52.520
because it really does draw the whole of the Psalm

62
00:02:52.560 --> 00:02:55.840
together as it prays for direction.

63
00:02:57.320 --> 00:02:59.680
One thing I've forgotten to be thankful about really

64
00:02:59.680 --> 00:03:02.280
in recent years is Google Maps.

65
00:03:03.640 --> 00:03:07.040
I remember years ago, like in the early days of marriage,

66
00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:10.200
like some of our most tense exchanges, if you will,

67
00:03:10.200 --> 00:03:11.520
had to do with directions.

68
00:03:11.520 --> 00:03:13.400
It was in the days of MapQuest.

69
00:03:13.400 --> 00:03:15.640
I don't know if any of you ever used MapQuest,

70
00:03:15.640 --> 00:03:18.040
but you have to print off all the directions

71
00:03:18.040 --> 00:03:19.520
and you print off 20 pages

72
00:03:19.520 --> 00:03:21.440
and you'd get to like page six

73
00:03:21.440 --> 00:03:23.240
and you'd take a wrong turn or something.

74
00:03:23.240 --> 00:03:25.320
And then you're completely thrown off

75
00:03:25.320 --> 00:03:27.160
and you don't know where you are

76
00:03:27.160 --> 00:03:29.160
and you're arguing back and forth.

77
00:03:30.400 --> 00:03:32.160
So it was not a great situation,

78
00:03:32.160 --> 00:03:33.760
but we should be thankful though.

79
00:03:33.760 --> 00:03:36.080
I mean, it was also the early days of GPS

80
00:03:36.080 --> 00:03:38.160
which that could lead you in an even more dangerous

81
00:03:38.160 --> 00:03:40.080
situation, people driving into rivers

82
00:03:40.080 --> 00:03:42.440
or on railroad tracks or off cliffs

83
00:03:42.440 --> 00:03:44.800
as we figured that out.

84
00:03:46.560 --> 00:03:48.040
We need direction.

85
00:03:48.040 --> 00:03:50.040
And we certainly need direction

86
00:03:50.040 --> 00:03:53.080
when it comes to the whole of life.

87
00:03:53.080 --> 00:03:57.000
And roads are probably the easiest thing to navigate.

88
00:03:57.000 --> 00:03:59.920
We need to be guided in all kinds of ways.

89
00:03:59.920 --> 00:04:04.920
And so Psalm five points us to the most reliable guide.

90
00:04:05.200 --> 00:04:07.440
So let's read verse eight again.

91
00:04:07.440 --> 00:04:11.080
It says, lead me, oh Lord, in your righteousness

92
00:04:11.080 --> 00:04:13.120
because of my enemies.

93
00:04:13.120 --> 00:04:15.680
Make your way straight before me.

94
00:04:16.520 --> 00:04:18.400
So David's praying for guidance.

95
00:04:18.400 --> 00:04:20.400
Notice the type of guidance he's praying for here.

96
00:04:20.400 --> 00:04:23.280
He's not praying about what he should do for the future

97
00:04:23.280 --> 00:04:26.800
like in terms of like vocation or where to go to school

98
00:04:26.800 --> 00:04:28.600
you know that kind of thing.

99
00:04:28.600 --> 00:04:30.560
The Lord guides us in those things

100
00:04:30.560 --> 00:04:32.600
and it's good for us to consider that together

101
00:04:32.600 --> 00:04:34.240
and another time we will look into that.

102
00:04:34.240 --> 00:04:37.600
But here, David is praying for a type of guidance

103
00:04:37.600 --> 00:04:39.880
that's even more crucial.

104
00:04:39.880 --> 00:04:44.280
It's a prayer that he would be guided in righteousness.

105
00:04:44.280 --> 00:04:47.680
It's a prayer that God would show him his ways.

106
00:04:49.040 --> 00:04:51.560
It's literally what we just prayed in the Lord's prayer.

107
00:04:51.560 --> 00:04:55.520
Lead us not into temptation but deliver us from evil.

108
00:04:55.520 --> 00:04:57.880
To put it positively it would be lead us

109
00:04:57.880 --> 00:05:00.240
in your righteousness.

110
00:05:00.240 --> 00:05:02.880
So Lord show me your ways is what Moses prayed

111
00:05:02.880 --> 00:05:05.840
that I may know you.

112
00:05:05.840 --> 00:05:08.600
So whatever decisions we make about other areas of life

113
00:05:08.600 --> 00:05:10.600
as we pray for guidance in those things

114
00:05:10.600 --> 00:05:14.160
we need to recognize this is what is most important.

115
00:05:14.160 --> 00:05:15.400
Knowing the righteousness of God

116
00:05:15.400 --> 00:05:17.760
and as we walk in his righteousness

117
00:05:17.760 --> 00:05:20.200
we can be sure that he will guide us

118
00:05:20.200 --> 00:05:22.920
in every area of life.

119
00:05:22.920 --> 00:05:26.000
So I'm just gonna draw your attention to three things

120
00:05:26.000 --> 00:05:29.320
from this Psalm that we need to know

121
00:05:29.320 --> 00:05:32.160
if we're going to follow after this path of righteousness

122
00:05:32.160 --> 00:05:34.400
that is laid before us.

123
00:05:34.400 --> 00:05:36.640
So as we pray, lead me in your righteousness.

124
00:05:36.640 --> 00:05:38.160
We need to know that this is also something

125
00:05:38.160 --> 00:05:41.800
we're praying that we would submit to the reign of God.

126
00:05:41.800 --> 00:05:43.880
So that's the first thing, submit to the reign of God.

127
00:05:43.880 --> 00:05:46.640
So all day long, David is being referred to

128
00:05:46.640 --> 00:05:48.400
by the people around him as King.

129
00:05:48.400 --> 00:05:49.840
He is King David.

130
00:05:49.840 --> 00:05:53.280
But when he prays he recognizes that there is a King

131
00:05:53.280 --> 00:05:54.480
that is higher than him.

132
00:05:54.480 --> 00:05:57.040
So he prays in verse two.

133
00:05:57.040 --> 00:06:00.520
He calls the Lord my King and my God.

134
00:06:00.520 --> 00:06:02.440
Give attention to the sound of my crime,

135
00:06:02.440 --> 00:06:05.040
my King and my God.

136
00:06:05.040 --> 00:06:08.240
So he speaks about the kingship of God.

137
00:06:08.240 --> 00:06:11.640
So calling God King is a recognition

138
00:06:11.640 --> 00:06:14.680
of his absolute authority.

139
00:06:14.680 --> 00:06:16.600
He is the sovereign King.

140
00:06:16.600 --> 00:06:18.800
There's a rich tradition of hymns

141
00:06:18.800 --> 00:06:21.640
where it literally refers to God as our God and King

142
00:06:21.640 --> 00:06:23.280
just like David has here.

143
00:06:23.280 --> 00:06:27.480
So sometimes here we sing all creatures of our God and King.

144
00:06:27.480 --> 00:06:29.680
That's coming right from scripture.

145
00:06:29.680 --> 00:06:34.400
So even in the Lord's prayer, we prayed our Father in heaven.

146
00:06:34.400 --> 00:06:36.640
So when we say in heaven, what are we actually saying

147
00:06:36.640 --> 00:06:37.720
when we say our Father in heaven?

148
00:06:37.720 --> 00:06:39.000
When we kind of think about the Father part

149
00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:40.400
but not necessarily the in heaven part,

150
00:06:40.400 --> 00:06:43.300
we're recognizing the authority of God.

151
00:06:43.300 --> 00:06:44.640
He reigns.

152
00:06:44.640 --> 00:06:45.680
That's what we're saying when we're saying

153
00:06:45.680 --> 00:06:46.520
our God in heaven.

154
00:06:46.520 --> 00:06:48.140
Therefore it follows, we then pray,

155
00:06:48.140 --> 00:06:49.320
hallowed be your name.

156
00:06:49.320 --> 00:06:54.320
In other words, be recognized for who you truly are.

157
00:06:55.940 --> 00:06:57.440
Well, who is he?

158
00:06:57.440 --> 00:07:00.280
Your kingdom come, your will be done

159
00:07:00.280 --> 00:07:01.520
on earth as it is in heaven.

160
00:07:01.520 --> 00:07:03.440
He's the King who has a kingdom.

161
00:07:03.440 --> 00:07:06.040
He's the King who reigns over all things in heaven

162
00:07:06.040 --> 00:07:08.080
and on earth.

163
00:07:08.080 --> 00:07:10.320
And he's the King whether we like it or not.

164
00:07:10.320 --> 00:07:13.120
You know, to get into politics,

165
00:07:13.120 --> 00:07:14.440
which is I'm sure what you all

166
00:07:14.440 --> 00:07:15.800
we're looking forward to today.

167
00:07:15.920 --> 00:07:18.360
No matter who is president,

168
00:07:18.360 --> 00:07:20.160
no matter it was the right or the left here

169
00:07:20.160 --> 00:07:22.320
and there will always be a yard sign somewhere

170
00:07:22.320 --> 00:07:24.360
that says not my president.

171
00:07:24.360 --> 00:07:26.360
It doesn't matter if it's on the Democrat side

172
00:07:26.360 --> 00:07:27.840
or Republican or whatever,

173
00:07:27.840 --> 00:07:29.080
people have that kind of sentiment

174
00:07:29.080 --> 00:07:30.560
like they're not my president

175
00:07:30.560 --> 00:07:32.960
whether they actually are or not.

176
00:07:32.960 --> 00:07:35.000
That's the sentiment that is here.

177
00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:37.840
So here's the truth I'm saying that points to.

178
00:07:37.840 --> 00:07:40.620
God is King whether or not we recognize him

179
00:07:40.620 --> 00:07:42.120
as the absolute authority.

180
00:07:42.120 --> 00:07:44.480
He is Lord.

181
00:07:44.480 --> 00:07:46.200
I know sometimes we might talk about making him

182
00:07:46.200 --> 00:07:47.120
Lord of your life.

183
00:07:47.120 --> 00:07:48.720
He is Lord.

184
00:07:48.720 --> 00:07:50.280
That includes your life too.

185
00:07:50.280 --> 00:07:52.480
Now the question is whether or not we will bow the knee

186
00:07:52.480 --> 00:07:55.400
and recognize him for who he truly is.

187
00:07:55.400 --> 00:07:58.800
He is the Lord whether we like it or not.

188
00:07:58.800 --> 00:08:02.400
So are we submitting to his his kingship?

189
00:08:04.160 --> 00:08:06.000
So this speaks to not just his kingship

190
00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:07.200
but how we approach him.

191
00:08:07.200 --> 00:08:09.780
Right, so we're submitting to the reign of the King.

192
00:08:09.780 --> 00:08:12.560
So how do we approach him in prayerful submission?

193
00:08:12.560 --> 00:08:13.960
Remember this is a prayer

194
00:08:13.960 --> 00:08:16.600
and this prayer is an invitation to bow our knee

195
00:08:16.600 --> 00:08:18.200
before the Lord as King

196
00:08:18.200 --> 00:08:21.360
and confess in prayer that he is Lord.

197
00:08:21.360 --> 00:08:24.760
You see this as well in what David says next.

198
00:08:24.760 --> 00:08:29.240
He says, oh Lord, in the morning you hear my voice.

199
00:08:29.240 --> 00:08:34.240
In the morning I prepare a sacrifice for you and watch.

200
00:08:34.520 --> 00:08:36.040
When you bring a sacrifice,

201
00:08:36.040 --> 00:08:39.260
you're saying that you no longer have ownership

202
00:08:39.260 --> 00:08:41.000
of the thing you are bringing.

203
00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:45.220
You're giving it over completely in sacrifice.

204
00:08:46.840 --> 00:08:50.120
This is what we do when we rightly pray.

205
00:08:50.120 --> 00:08:52.560
We are bringing our lives before the Lord

206
00:08:52.560 --> 00:08:55.600
in complete surrender.

207
00:08:55.600 --> 00:08:57.080
So Jesus calls his disciples.

208
00:08:57.080 --> 00:08:59.960
So Luke chapter nine verse 23

209
00:08:59.960 --> 00:09:03.360
to take up their cross daily and follow him.

210
00:09:03.360 --> 00:09:06.720
Like surrender your life daily afresh to the Lord.

211
00:09:06.720 --> 00:09:07.680
My life is not my own.

212
00:09:07.680 --> 00:09:09.880
It belongs to you.

213
00:09:09.920 --> 00:09:11.480
All right, so this is a morning psalm.

214
00:09:11.480 --> 00:09:14.560
So David is bringing his prayers to the Lord

215
00:09:14.560 --> 00:09:15.400
in the morning.

216
00:09:15.400 --> 00:09:18.160
So like David it's good to bring our day

217
00:09:18.160 --> 00:09:20.160
and our lives before the Lord each morning

218
00:09:20.160 --> 00:09:25.160
and say your kingdom come, your will be done.

219
00:09:25.560 --> 00:09:27.300
So there's prayerful submission here

220
00:09:27.300 --> 00:09:30.100
but there's also a kind of hopeful expectation.

221
00:09:30.100 --> 00:09:33.040
Notice what he says when he lays down his sacrifice

222
00:09:33.040 --> 00:09:34.520
before the Lord he says he lays it down

223
00:09:34.520 --> 00:09:36.280
and he watches.

224
00:09:36.360 --> 00:09:37.800
He says now I watch.

225
00:09:37.800 --> 00:09:40.360
That's hopeful expectation.

226
00:09:40.360 --> 00:09:42.440
So as we submit to God's reign

227
00:09:42.440 --> 00:09:44.840
we do so in the hopeful expectation

228
00:09:44.840 --> 00:09:48.760
or anticipation that he will do what is right.

229
00:09:50.080 --> 00:09:52.760
He is our Father in heaven.

230
00:09:52.760 --> 00:09:55.040
And so we can know that he is our Father.

231
00:09:55.040 --> 00:09:57.800
He's willing to do what is best

232
00:09:57.800 --> 00:09:59.800
but also as the one in heaven as the King

233
00:09:59.800 --> 00:10:02.920
he is able to bring about all the good

234
00:10:02.920 --> 00:10:04.560
that he promises.

235
00:10:04.560 --> 00:10:06.320
He's the sovereign King who can bring about

236
00:10:06.320 --> 00:10:09.880
all the good he promises in our lives.

237
00:10:09.880 --> 00:10:11.840
So a wonderful passage to go to

238
00:10:11.840 --> 00:10:13.600
which I know many of you will be familiar with

239
00:10:13.600 --> 00:10:16.120
is Romans 828 where Paul speaks

240
00:10:16.120 --> 00:10:17.320
with that kind of assurance.

241
00:10:17.320 --> 00:10:21.000
He says for we know that all things

242
00:10:21.000 --> 00:10:23.320
work together for the good of those who love God

243
00:10:23.320 --> 00:10:27.200
to those who are the called according to his purpose.

244
00:10:27.200 --> 00:10:29.920
Now that doesn't mean all things work together

245
00:10:29.920 --> 00:10:30.760
for good.

246
00:10:30.760 --> 00:10:33.200
It doesn't mean that everything that happens is good

247
00:10:33.200 --> 00:10:35.520
and that doesn't mean just wait a few minutes

248
00:10:35.520 --> 00:10:37.640
and everything is going to all of a sudden resolve

249
00:10:37.640 --> 00:10:41.520
like the stereotypical Christian movie

250
00:10:41.520 --> 00:10:43.560
where the team wins the game at the end

251
00:10:43.560 --> 00:10:45.040
and the coach gets a brand new truck

252
00:10:45.040 --> 00:10:46.360
and everything is just right

253
00:10:46.360 --> 00:10:49.760
because all things work together for the good after all.

254
00:10:51.120 --> 00:10:53.840
The thing is we can't fully grasp the kind of good

255
00:10:53.840 --> 00:10:55.880
that's being spoken of in Romans 828

256
00:10:55.880 --> 00:10:58.080
and let you see Romans 829.

257
00:10:59.680 --> 00:11:01.360
That tells us what good purpose

258
00:11:01.360 --> 00:11:03.000
the Lord is bringing about.

259
00:11:03.000 --> 00:11:07.160
God is bringing about conformity to the likeness of his son.

260
00:11:07.160 --> 00:11:09.360
So what is the good that God is at work

261
00:11:09.360 --> 00:11:11.840
in all things to bring about in our lives?

262
00:11:12.880 --> 00:11:16.640
Conformity to his son is what it says in Romans 829.

263
00:11:16.640 --> 00:11:20.400
In other words, he is at work in all things for our good

264
00:11:20.400 --> 00:11:25.080
in order that we might be led in his righteousness.

265
00:11:25.080 --> 00:11:29.760
So we pray Lord lead me in your righteousness

266
00:11:29.760 --> 00:11:30.680
in all things.

267
00:11:31.680 --> 00:11:35.480
Okay, so we submit to the reign of God

268
00:11:35.480 --> 00:11:39.360
but also secondly, for it's going to be led in his righteousness

269
00:11:39.360 --> 00:11:42.120
we must revere the holiness of God.

270
00:11:43.120 --> 00:11:44.800
Revere the holiness of God.

271
00:11:44.800 --> 00:11:46.520
All right, so context here.

272
00:11:46.520 --> 00:11:49.040
David is groaning before the Lord.

273
00:11:49.040 --> 00:11:51.360
You see that in verse one.

274
00:11:52.360 --> 00:11:54.480
