307
00:13:19.140 --> 00:13:21.640
So he's approaching God assured of his love

308
00:13:21.640 --> 00:13:24.520
but he's also approaching God with a fear

309
00:13:24.560 --> 00:13:28.760
or a reverence knowing that God is also holy.

310
00:13:30.320 --> 00:13:32.520
So what does it mean to say that God is holy?

311
00:13:32.520 --> 00:13:34.720
Well, let's just take the descriptions that he gives us.

312
00:13:34.720 --> 00:13:35.880
So verse four.

313
00:13:37.320 --> 00:13:39.520
God is displeased with sin.

314
00:13:39.520 --> 00:13:41.720
He does not delight in wickedness.

315
00:13:42.620 --> 00:13:44.000
So we're tempted to sin.

316
00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:44.840
Why?

317
00:13:44.840 --> 00:13:46.760
Because it's desirable for us.

318
00:13:46.760 --> 00:13:49.040
We want it.

319
00:13:49.040 --> 00:13:50.760
But it's not desirable to God.

320
00:13:50.760 --> 00:13:51.680
Not even for a second.

321
00:13:51.680 --> 00:13:55.240
He doesn't take any pleasure in sin.

322
00:13:56.440 --> 00:14:00.040
But also we see that God will not dwell with evil either.

323
00:14:00.040 --> 00:14:03.240
So his presence, his dwelling place, his a holy place.

324
00:14:03.240 --> 00:14:06.900
Evil may not dwell with you, it says in verse four.

325
00:14:06.900 --> 00:14:09.400
So evil is never at home with God,

326
00:14:09.400 --> 00:14:11.120
not even for a second.

327
00:14:11.120 --> 00:14:13.520
This is why it says in Habakkuk 1.13,

328
00:14:13.520 --> 00:14:17.960
your eyes are too pure to look on evil.

329
00:14:18.960 --> 00:14:22.640
So if that is the holiness of God in relation to sin,

330
00:14:22.640 --> 00:14:24.920
what about people who commit sin?

331
00:14:25.840 --> 00:14:28.520
Let's read verse five again.

332
00:14:28.520 --> 00:14:32.440
Says the boastful shall not stand before your eyes.

333
00:14:32.440 --> 00:14:35.800
You hate all evildoers.

334
00:14:37.360 --> 00:14:40.880
Well, one of the good things,

335
00:14:40.880 --> 00:14:43.740
but hard things about preaching through books

336
00:14:43.740 --> 00:14:46.400
of the Bible like this is it makes us look

337
00:14:46.400 --> 00:14:51.160
at hard truths that are difficult to understand

338
00:14:51.160 --> 00:14:54.720
or truths that make us uncomfortable.

339
00:14:54.720 --> 00:14:57.440
Let me tell you, what I just read is one of those,

340
00:14:57.440 --> 00:15:02.440
at least for me, or you hate all evildoers.

341
00:15:03.000 --> 00:15:04.840
Like I've preached a general series

342
00:15:04.840 --> 00:15:05.680
through the Psalms before

343
00:15:05.680 --> 00:15:07.640
and let me tell you which Psalm I skipped.

344
00:15:07.640 --> 00:15:11.240
It was Psalm five and a few others.

345
00:15:11.240 --> 00:15:13.620
There are 150 Psalms.

346
00:15:13.620 --> 00:15:16.200
So what do we do with a passage like this?

347
00:15:16.320 --> 00:15:18.400
First of all, I mean, know that God doesn't need

348
00:15:18.400 --> 00:15:20.440
our kind of PR support, right?

349
00:15:20.440 --> 00:15:23.740
He doesn't need that from us.

350
00:15:23.740 --> 00:15:25.680
Let me just call us back to that kind of first point

351
00:15:25.680 --> 00:15:26.760
we're seeing about his kingship.

352
00:15:26.760 --> 00:15:29.720
We need to submit to the authority of God.

353
00:15:29.720 --> 00:15:32.280
And how does the king reign?

354
00:15:32.280 --> 00:15:35.720
He reigns, he governs by his word.

355
00:15:35.720 --> 00:15:37.760
So to submit to the authority of God

356
00:15:37.760 --> 00:15:40.480
is to submit to his word, to all of it,

357
00:15:40.480 --> 00:15:42.760
even the parts we may not understand

358
00:15:42.760 --> 00:15:45.220
or that make us uncomfortable.

359
00:15:46.100 --> 00:15:48.140
So we need to sit with what it says here.

360
00:15:49.180 --> 00:15:50.780
