364
00:16:01.460 --> 00:16:04.060
We'll get to some encouraging news in a second

365
00:16:04.060 --> 00:16:07.100
but let's sit with this for a moment.

366
00:16:08.380 --> 00:16:09.420
Because without realizing it,

367
00:16:09.420 --> 00:16:12.340
we can have a distorted view of God

368
00:16:12.820 --> 00:16:15.500
where we like certain verses of the Bible

369
00:16:15.500 --> 00:16:18.300
and that's all that we think about in relation to God

370
00:16:18.300 --> 00:16:20.500
and but we don't see the whole of scripture,

371
00:16:20.500 --> 00:16:22.220
this entire picture of God.

372
00:16:22.220 --> 00:16:23.380
So what does this mean?

373
00:16:23.380 --> 00:16:26.540
God hates all evil doers.

374
00:16:26.540 --> 00:16:27.820
What means, here's the truth,

375
00:16:27.820 --> 00:16:30.740
that God's righteous justice

376
00:16:30.740 --> 00:16:35.740
stands not only against evil but evil doers.

377
00:16:36.580 --> 00:16:39.020
Where you cannot fully separate out

378
00:16:40.020 --> 00:16:43.620
the actions from the person that commits those actions.

379
00:16:43.620 --> 00:16:47.380
If you go to a court for a crime that has been committed

380
00:16:47.380 --> 00:16:51.260
and the judge makes the sentence,

381
00:16:51.260 --> 00:16:52.540
he sentences you, right?

382
00:16:52.540 --> 00:16:54.260
He doesn't say like, oh, you stole this,

383
00:16:54.260 --> 00:16:57.820
so I'm gonna punish your thieving, your theft.

384
00:16:57.820 --> 00:17:01.300
No, you are the one who is punished for the crime.

385
00:17:01.300 --> 00:17:03.540
So it's true that God is against sin

386
00:17:03.540 --> 00:17:07.620
but also here, those who commit sin as well.

387
00:17:07.860 --> 00:17:09.540
He opposes not only sinful behavior

388
00:17:09.540 --> 00:17:13.240
but the very ones who carries out this behavior.

389
00:17:14.220 --> 00:17:17.700
Okay, so God's holy character is seen in his conduct.

390
00:17:18.540 --> 00:17:20.020
So what does it say in verse six?

391
00:17:20.020 --> 00:17:23.140
You destroy all those who speak lies.

392
00:17:23.140 --> 00:17:27.780
The Lord abhor is the bloodthirsty and deceitful man.

393
00:17:29.500 --> 00:17:32.860
We'll return to that in just a moment with some good news.

394
00:17:34.580 --> 00:17:36.780
But notice as well, not just the holiness of God,

395
00:17:36.780 --> 00:17:38.320
