401
00:17:53.380 --> 00:17:55.260
So we see all kinds of descriptions

402
00:17:55.260 --> 00:17:57.180
of like people's wickedness or evil

403
00:17:57.180 --> 00:18:00.660
or boastfulness, deceitfulness, violence.

404
00:18:00.660 --> 00:18:04.700
And he returns to this theme in verses nine and 10.

405
00:18:04.700 --> 00:18:05.700
And in verses nine and 10,

406
00:18:05.740 --> 00:18:08.740
there's a particular focus here.

407
00:18:08.740 --> 00:18:10.780
And it's showing that sin is,

408
00:18:10.780 --> 00:18:13.060
when it comes to the deadliness of sin,

409
00:18:13.060 --> 00:18:15.660
it points us particularly to the deceitfulness of sin

410
00:18:15.660 --> 00:18:18.220
and how that deceitfulness is what leads us

411
00:18:18.220 --> 00:18:20.740
to the deadliness of sin.

412
00:18:20.740 --> 00:18:22.980
So in verse nine, we see that they speak

413
00:18:22.980 --> 00:18:25.940
in flattering ways the enemies of David here.

414
00:18:25.940 --> 00:18:28.540
There's no truth in their mouths.

415
00:18:28.540 --> 00:18:31.020
Their words are deceitful.

416
00:18:32.140 --> 00:18:35.340
So I got to start thinking about this

417
00:18:35.500 --> 00:18:36.980
this week, if you were to think about like

418
00:18:36.980 --> 00:18:40.860
there being a stream that sin is then flowing from,

419
00:18:40.860 --> 00:18:44.060
you're to trace sin and all of its impact on humanity.

420
00:18:44.060 --> 00:18:46.420
Right back to the source, what would you find?

421
00:18:46.420 --> 00:18:47.720
Well, you go back to the Garden of Eden

422
00:18:47.720 --> 00:18:52.020
and you would find deceit, you would find a lie there.

423
00:18:52.020 --> 00:18:53.740
So you can take all of sin

424
00:18:53.740 --> 00:18:55.900
and put it in that category of deceit here.

425
00:18:55.900 --> 00:18:58.480
That's what it's all going back to.

426
00:18:59.460 --> 00:19:02.620
And so he then uses kind of graphic imagery here

427
00:19:02.620 --> 00:19:04.300
to describe the deadliness of sin.

428
00:19:05.140 --> 00:19:10.140
So on the front side of things, there's flattery.

429
00:19:10.340 --> 00:19:14.520
There's things that sounds maybe appealing or plausible,

430
00:19:14.520 --> 00:19:16.780
but he wants us to see that it's really deadly.

431
00:19:16.780 --> 00:19:21.300
He says their inmost self, verse nine is destruction.

432
00:19:21.300 --> 00:19:23.700
And their throat is like an open grave.

433
00:19:23.700 --> 00:19:26.400
So what they're saying may seem plausible or desirable,

434
00:19:26.400 --> 00:19:30.020
but it's coming from a place of spiritual death.

435
00:19:30.020 --> 00:19:31.860
It's a demonstration of the fact

436
00:19:31.860 --> 00:19:33.700
that someone is dead spiritually

437
00:19:33.700 --> 00:19:37.860
when they're speaking these falsehoods, these lies.

438
00:19:37.860 --> 00:19:41.140
So we saw in Ephesians two in verse one,

439
00:19:41.140 --> 00:19:45.820
speaks about us being dead in our trespasses and sins.

440
00:19:45.820 --> 00:19:47.660
All right, so things might sound good,

441
00:19:47.660 --> 00:19:49.860
but it's coming from a place of death.

442
00:19:49.860 --> 00:19:51.580
You might think of like, I don't know,

443
00:19:51.580 --> 00:19:53.340
a beautiful place like the Taj Mahal

444
00:19:53.340 --> 00:19:55.220
and you're like, well, what is this place?

445
00:19:55.220 --> 00:19:57.940
It's actually a grave, it's a tomb.

446
00:19:59.200 --> 00:20:01.300
So there's beauty, but death behind it.

447
00:20:02.220 --> 00:20:06.220
Death is ultimately God's judgment upon sin.

448
00:20:06.220 --> 00:20:09.340
It's being separated from life with him.

449
00:20:09.340 --> 00:20:13.500
It is being under his wrath.

450
00:20:13.500 --> 00:20:15.460
And David actually speaks here of God's judgment

