00:21:30.980 --> 00:21:33.420
and like flames at the bottom, you kind of see that,

477
00:21:33.420 --> 00:21:34.460
that kind of thing.

478
00:21:34.460 --> 00:21:37.220
That's not what he's calling us to do here.

479
00:21:37.220 --> 00:21:40.500
We're actually hit with a big dilemma.

480
00:21:40.500 --> 00:21:44.820
The fact is, we are all indicted by the things

481
00:21:44.820 --> 00:21:46.540
that he says here.

482
00:21:47.460 --> 00:21:50.180
When it comes to the holiness of God and our sinfulness,

483
00:21:50.180 --> 00:21:53.860
I recently heard a child say to his dad,

484
00:21:53.860 --> 00:21:55.620
he said, dad, in a war,

485
00:21:56.580 --> 00:21:59.260
are there always good guys and bad guys?

486
00:21:59.260 --> 00:22:01.420
You know, where it's kind of like one side or the other.

487
00:22:01.420 --> 00:22:03.540
And I thought, well, that is actually a pretty profound

488
00:22:03.540 --> 00:22:05.220
question to ask.

489
00:22:05.220 --> 00:22:07.220
And if we're reading a psalm like this as though,

490
00:22:07.220 --> 00:22:09.580
like, we're the good guys and other people out there

491
00:22:09.580 --> 00:22:12.660
are the bad guys, well, look again.

492
00:22:12.660 --> 00:22:17.260
This is who we all are apart from the mercy of God.

493
00:22:17.260 --> 00:22:19.860
This is what we all deserve.

494
00:22:20.900 --> 00:22:22.980
It's interesting, who wrote this?

495
00:22:22.980 --> 00:22:23.820
David.

496
00:22:23.820 --> 00:22:26.260
Kind of look at this checklist here and you're like,

497
00:22:26.260 --> 00:22:29.420
well, David, deceit.

498
00:22:29.420 --> 00:22:32.740
That sounds like something I've heard of you

499
00:22:32.740 --> 00:22:34.220
in Second Samuel.

500
00:22:34.220 --> 00:22:36.340
Right, so as you're working through these descriptions

501
00:22:36.340 --> 00:22:39.220
of sinfulness, these are descriptions of David,

502
00:22:39.220 --> 00:22:42.860
the very person who's praying these things.

503
00:22:42.860 --> 00:22:47.260
Right, so description that lines up with his own sin.

504
00:22:48.300 --> 00:22:49.980
And when you get to the New Testament,

505
00:22:49.980 --> 00:22:52.260
particularly Romans chapter three,

506
00:22:52.300 --> 00:22:55.660
which speaks about us all being sinful, you know.

507
00:22:55.660 --> 00:22:58.620
Romans 3, 23, all of sin and false short of the glory of God.

508
00:22:59.740 --> 00:23:03.940
It also quotes Psalm five in the description of sinfulness

509
00:23:03.940 --> 00:23:07.500
here to describe the whole of humanity.

510
00:23:07.500 --> 00:23:09.940
Fascinating, I was amazed to see that,

511
00:23:09.940 --> 00:23:12.180
oh, like his Psalm five quoted in the New Testament.

512
00:23:12.180 --> 00:23:15.780
Yes, in Romans three where it says this is all of us.

513
00:23:15.780 --> 00:23:16.620
Amazing.

514
00:23:17.780 --> 00:23:20.500
So if we're going to appreciate the salvation

515
00:23:20.580 --> 00:23:23.300
